00:16:48.370 --> 00:16:49.300
We are representing.

00:16:49.300 --> 00:16:50.500
We're responsible.

00:16:50.500 --> 00:16:53.950
Wherever we are, we are
responsible to hold up

00:16:53.950 --> 00:16:56.530
who we are and
our whole culture.

00:16:56.530 --> 00:16:59.530
Whether we're the only
Chicana in the room

00:16:59.530 --> 00:17:03.929
at a function in a very astute
place, we're representing.

00:17:03.929 --> 00:17:04.720
SPEAKER: Of course.

00:17:04.720 --> 00:17:05.140
YOLANDA GONZALEZ:
It doesn't matter

00:17:05.140 --> 00:17:08.380
if you're in the restroom or
if you're in the dining room,

00:17:08.380 --> 00:17:09.490
people watch.

00:17:09.490 --> 00:17:11.920
And you have to represent
who your culture is.

00:17:11.920 --> 00:17:13.339
SPEAKER: Absolutely.

00:17:13.339 --> 00:17:14.618
YOLANDA GONZALEZ: Very-- yeah.

00:17:14.618 --> 00:17:16.780
SANDRA CORNEJO: And Los
Angeles, just in general--

00:17:16.780 --> 00:17:19.900
like I've moved around a
bit, and I've experienced

00:17:19.900 --> 00:17:22.599
