I think it's
important to mentor.

00:19:42.130 --> 00:19:44.770
I've taught several places
throughout the 30 years

00:19:44.770 --> 00:19:46.260
that I've been creating art.

00:19:46.260 --> 00:19:50.340
I worked for Plaza
de la Raza teaching

00:19:50.340 --> 00:19:55.300
and for Para Los Ninos for
inner city arts for 14 years.

00:19:55.300 --> 00:19:57.910
And it was amazing to
work with the youth

00:19:57.910 --> 00:20:02.290
and just to teach them
art but to also teach them

00:20:02.290 --> 00:20:05.830
acceptance of who they are.

00:20:05.830 --> 00:20:09.205
Right now, I work
with [INAUDIBLE]

00:20:09.205 --> 00:20:13.720
teaching senior citizens
watercolor and ceramics.

00:20:13.720 --> 00:20:15.134
SPEAKER: Hence, your AARP?

00:20:15.134 --> 00:20:16.050
YOLANDA GONZALEZ: Yes.

00:20:16.050 --> 00:20:18.530
And they're absolutely lovely.

00:20:18.530 --> 00:20:19.690
SPEAKER: That's nice.

00:20:19.690 --> 00:20:21.940
And so you were here recently.

00:20:21.940 --> 00:20:23.680
You're saying three
years ago, right?

00:20:23.680 --> 00:20:25.360
SANDRA CORNEJO: Yeah.

