Romero, another artist

00:20:46.180 --> 00:20:47.950
in the community--

00:20:47.950 --> 00:20:51.080
I would assist them within their
classes at Plaza de la Raza.

00:20:51.080 --> 00:20:53.680
And I realized that
there was really

00:20:53.680 --> 00:20:57.010
nothing being offered for
the next generation that's

00:20:57.010 --> 00:20:59.080
trying to move
forward and kind of

00:20:59.080 --> 00:21:01.690
like hone in on their skills,
what they're really trying

00:21:01.690 --> 00:21:03.500
to say and express,
and just like start

00:21:03.500 --> 00:21:07.030
developing their own style,
their own voice through art.

00:21:07.030 --> 00:21:10.960
So I proposed a portfolio
preparation course at Plaza.

00:21:10.960 --> 00:21:13.690
And we're entering the
fourth semester now.

00:21:13.690 --> 00:21:16.600
So I'm pretty excited about it.

00:21:16.600 --> 00:21:20.410
We have many beautiful,
very talented artists.

00:21:20.410 --> 00:21:24.250
And just giving them a space
to really think about the work

00:21:24.250 --> 00:21:27.909
that they're making and have
them develop their style,

00:21:27.909 --> 00:21:29.950
that was something that
was very important for me

00:21:29.950 --> 00:21:33.417
as a kid in high school,
like having that teacher that

00:21:33.417 --> 00:21:35.500
will just kind of will
give you the space and room

00:21:35.500 --> 00:21:37.650
to do what you need to do.

00:21:37.650 --> 00:21:40.780
And you know, just like
beginning dialogue,

00:21:40.780 --> 00:21:43.180
having conversations
about your work.

